reviews_data.review_text: Delicious coffee! There's so much to see in the connected boutique. Love the bookstore.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for stopping by & sharing 🫶🏼 so glad you enjoyed your coffee while you were sippin’ + shoppin’

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful new coffee place! Arrived bright and Early at 7 pm and was pleasantly surprised to see that this location was not hard to find, especially being around the Central Ave location. I failed to get the lady's name but she was so friendly, attentive, and gave great recommendations. The place itself is super cute and chic! They have a small table near the entrance to sit and enjoy your coffee, they have a library room with plenty of books and seating as well as another back room with candles and jewelry. If I didn't have to go to work, I could've spent a good hour enjoying my coffee and browsing through all they had to offer. I ordered their shaken espresso with vanilla and it was DELICIOUS!!!!!!!!! I can't wait to return and try some of their ordered lattes on the menu.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Yessss! A place to come, stay, & BE! You come back soon & spend the day with us 🫶🏼

reviews_data.review_text:
I’m thrilled to have stumbled upon this charming coffee shop with such delightful treasures. They’ve got candles, wall art, books, jewelry, and more! Upon entering, I was warmly greeted and instantly captivated by the cozy atmosphere. The delightful aroma and beautifully decorated space made it an absolute delight. And let me tell you, the seating options are simply lovely!

I thoroughly enjoyed the royal crumb drink. It was incredibly delicious and sweetened to perfection. The pastry I ordered was so delectable that I couldn’t resist devouring it.

What a great find and I’d definitely come back again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Tameka! We loved having you stop in & spend some time with us 🫶🏼 thanks for sharing!

reviews_data.review_text:
CHNO Coffee is an adorable little spot with a small but mighty menu of coffee and espresso drinks. Most of today's "Eclipse" was enjoyed (stolen) by the lovely Mrs. K. and I did get a couple of sips. White chocolate and mocha and coffee. Iced and creamy, rich, delicious. Perfect on a warm Charlotte afternoon.

It's not a very big shop - you're probably not handing around all day with your laptop. But it's a really good dose of caffeine and our barista today was super nice and super friendly. I am absolutely sure that we'll be back!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.owner_answer: What’s yours is hers, right? 😂 Love that you both got to enjoy some time together here at the shop with us!

reviews_data.review_text:
Great spot for a morning coffee! Very local for those in Plaza Midwood, I was able to stop by on the way to work to grab an iced latte. It's definitely off the beaten path, but once inside it has great bounce, with one room bright and the other darker, so you can pick which speaks to you more; definitely a cute little place to sit and relax, enjoy a book or connect to the Internet for work.
The latte was superb, and they have a ton of flavored options if that's your thing as well.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for making us apart of your day & sharing how your visit was 🫶🏼 We’re so glad you enjoyed the latte & our new space! Hope to see you back soon

reviews_data.review_text:
I was blown away in the best possible way. The exterior does not do it justice. However, there is plenty of parking to make up for it. The owner also expressed plans to add more outside to welcome people. Yet, you are immediately transported to a magical oasis as soon as you open the door.
While the drinks and food were great, the decor and crafts still the show. Everything from the flooring and wall paint to the differences in room themes is carefully crafted.
The bookstore, while small, was packed with something for everyone, including children. In addition to books, there were crafts for sale by local vendors.
My favorite room was the back sitting area. They painted the walls in a moody shade of blue. There is a variety of seating options as well as additional crafts for sale. This is a must try!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your visit & super thoughtful review 🥰 we loved meeting you & hope to see you all back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious lattes, great staff, and a beautiful store with many local artists and local vendors. They had books, ceramics, plants, clothes, kids things, purses, soap, a man cave, candles, oils, etc! A great stop for a cute gift!
Coffee taste really good & price is reasonable
Awesome coffee and great staff.
I had their cold brew at an event and man that's some good coffee. I'll definitely be coming by!
Had the best lavender latte I have ever had here. Looking forward to exploring the rest of the menu!
Delicious 😋
Delicious coffee, kind owner, so nice to be attached to crown & honey!
Chno coffee is a cute little coffee shop inside a boutique. It’s SO good and is super quick! They also have tons of parking.

CHNO has become my favorite place to get coffee in the city.
The Chai is perfectly spiced
Matcha is very merry.
And the coffee always hits the spot!
Great place and vibe. I will be coming back again!
Tried CHNO coffee at the Crown and Honey boutique  location. So tasty and they are super nice! I had the lavender coffee. Will be back for sure!
Had the cotton candy latte in one of their beautiful for here mugs!! So delicious and amazing people!!
Un lugar cargado de amabilidad

My favorite coffee shop! I love that they open early enough to swing by before school starts and whether I get chai or coffee it’s incredible and keeps me caffeinated for my day. Carlea is so incredibly friendly and provides the best service.
Best Coffee!

Literal best coffee in town! This place is my new addiction in the best way! I’ve been around the block of coffee shops, and this is hands down the best. And Carlea is the sweetest around! I recommend this coffee shop to everyone 💕

Great coffee in the local Crown and Honey LLC boutique! Very cute and relaxing environment that has all the right vibes for shopping as well as taking some time to wind down after it all. Highly recommend exploring!

Yall, if you haven’t been here yet.. RUN, don’t walk! I am not even a big coffee drinker but everything I’ve had from CHNO coffee is amazingggg! Lavender lattes, sweet little iced coffees, everything! Also, it helps that the owner is the sweetest, most hard working soul.

Stop going to Starbucks and dunkin, go support your local mamas hustling and making us yummy drinks!
We love chno coffee, I’ve gotten it at events before and it’s SO GOOD! The owner is such a sweetheart and I love supporting a small business. Definitely recommend checking her out!!

CHNO has the BEST coffee I have ever had! That’s coming from someone that visits different cafes in CLT. The coffee is 100/10 and the owner is one of the sweetest person I have ever met! You can immediately tell she’s very passionate and loves what she does. I cannot rave enough about this place. Give it a try and I just know you won’t be disappointed!!
Best coffee in the CLT area! Carlea is the sweetest person in the world💖✨
Cozy, friendly, warm and amazing staff. Love the coffee.!
The best coffee shop in Indian Trail! I'm so glad they found a permanent home in Crown & Honey Botique on 74. Everyone is super friendly and their coffee is wonderful ❤️
This is the cutest little spot, everyone is so friendly, & the coffee is delicious :)

Awesome shop! Was bored, decided to take the drive down to check it out since they opened brick-and-mortar. Royal Crumb was amazing, and the service was great too. On my next road trip heading south, I can't wait to check it out again!
Amazing customer service and delicious coffee!!! I love supporting local coffee shops.

CHNO Coffee Company is a warm and inviting place. They're inside Crown and Honey.
Dara, was pleasant and friendly explaining to me all the beverage choices. I purchased a medium drip coffee, made perfectly and a beautiful porcelain mug made by Latin Lotus Pottery.
I recommend the Royal Crumb Latte.  Also get some CHNO coffee beans to go.
The BEST  coffee I’ve ever had. Absolutely delicious. Find one of her popups and try it out, it’s a local must.
Absolutely the most delicious coffee I’ve ever had! Completely beats out Starbucks in taste, price and customer service! I can’t wait to find all their events and show up for a coffee ✨
reviews_data.owner_answer: You know we love seeing you at our events!! 🫶🏼 thanks for the love!

reviews_data.review_text:
I am new to the Charlotte area and have recently discovered CHNO coffee. Their cold brews are delicious and reasonably priced. My favorite is a white chocolate and also vanilla rose which is light. They also deliver and have weekly baked goods. Definitely coming back for more !

The owners are really friendly and knowledgeable which is a plus <3
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!! Glad we get to be a bright part of your move to CLT!
